[5] Virginia - fox, human exposure
Date: 22 Mar 2016
Source: Daily Progress [edited]
http://www.dailyprogress.com/news/police-fox-that-bit-charlottesville-woman-had-rabies/article_b0eb899c-f051-11e5-b85e-4ba64a33e6a0.html


A fox that Charlottesville police caught after it bit someone last week was found to be infected with rabies, police said Tuesday [22 Mar 2016]. Police said they have informed the victim of the test result.

This was the 3rd aggressive fox sighting in Charlottesville during March 2016.

On 7 Mar 2016, police said a "suspicious fox" was seen in the downtown area, where it reportedly bit 2 different people. That fox has not yet been caught.

Then, on 14 Mar 2016, a 2nd fox was caught and put down by police after it acted aggressively toward officers. That fox also was sent to the health department, but it tested negative for rabies.

