[6] Massachusetts - fox, human exposure
Date: 18 Mar 2016
Source: WWLP.com [edited]
http://wwlp.com/2016/03/18/fox-that-attacked-2-in-leicester-had-rabies/


A sick fox that attacked 2 Leicester residents last week had rabies.

Police in the central Massachusetts town are now urging residents to get their pets vaccinated and have even scheduled a rabies clinic on 2 Apr 2016.

They also warned that the rabid fox could have infected other animals.

Police say the fox attacked 2 people in the same neighborhood within about a 20-minute period on 10 Mar 2016. The next day, what was believed to be the same fox was killed by police when it was spotted near a school.

It was sent to the state lab for testing, and police on Thursday [17 Mar 2016] confirmed the positive rabies test.

